{{No footnotes|date=March 2018}} '''Clan and Title System''' (氏姓制度, Shisei Seido) refers to the system in ancient [[Japan]] where central [[nobles]] and, subsequently, regional [[chieftains]] were granted clan names (氏, Uji) and titles (姓, Kabane) by the [[Yamato Court]] based on their contributions to the state and political standing. These titles were hereditary and signified a privileged status. It is also referred to as the "Clan and Title System" (ウヂ・カバネの制).
